1
00:02:56,560 --> 00:02:57,480
Gosh.

2
00:02:59,320 --> 00:03:02,640
As her father, I‘d like to invite you

3
00:03:02,720 --> 00:03:05,720
to my daughter's wedding
with Mr. Wayu Buranachat.

4
00:03:09,760 --> 00:03:11,640
If you love me,

5
00:03:11,720 --> 00:03:13,520
can I ask you something?

6
00:03:13,600 --> 00:03:15,040
Leave them.

7
00:03:15,120 --> 00:03:16,280
You should love your brother

8
00:03:17,320 --> 00:03:19,240
and be good to him as much as you can,

9
00:03:20,600 --> 00:03:21,760
while you still have the chance.

10
00:03:21,840 --> 00:03:26,080
I'll never let this wedding happen.

11
00:03:26,160 --> 00:03:29,480
I ask everyone to begin voting now.

12
00:03:29,560 --> 00:03:31,000
What about your father's businesses?

13
00:03:31,080 --> 00:03:32,960
I'm not suited for them,

14
00:03:33,040 --> 00:03:35,040
so I shut them down.

15
00:03:35,120 --> 00:03:36,120
I believe we're in an era

16
00:03:36,200 --> 00:03:39,320
where we can build businesses
by giving back to society.

17
00:03:43,720 --> 00:03:46,480
Then take me to meet your family

18
00:03:46,560 --> 00:03:48,280
and get to know them properly.

19
00:03:51,080 --> 00:03:53,120
I heard you wanted
to get to know our family.

20
00:03:53,200 --> 00:03:55,320
Everyone here is like family to us.

21
00:03:55,920 --> 00:03:57,840
I hope you don't mind.

22
00:03:58,760 --> 00:04:02,440
I feel really honored and happy
to meet everyone.

23
00:04:06,760 --> 00:04:08,480
This kind of vibe,

24
00:04:08,560 --> 00:04:10,920
even without snow,
as long as there's chicken and beer,

25
00:04:11,000 --> 00:04:14,120
Chicmaek, that's enough.

26
00:04:16,040 --> 00:04:17,160
<i>Annyeong haseyo.</i>

27
00:04:18,440 --> 00:04:19,399
<i>Annyeong maseyo.</i>

28
00:04:19,480 --> 00:04:21,480
<i>Anseong saseyo</i>--
Hey, what am I even saying?

29
00:04:21,560 --> 00:04:23,560
What "seyo"?

30
00:04:23,640 --> 00:04:24,560
<i>Annyeong haseyo.</i>

31
00:04:26,760 --> 00:04:29,920
You're like an <i>oppa</i>.

32
00:04:33,520 --> 00:04:35,320
Here we go!

33
00:04:36,480 --> 00:04:39,200
Ice-cold beer and hot chicken,
coming right up, beautiful ladies.

34
00:04:40,240 --> 00:04:41,600
You're so beautiful.

35
00:04:42,280 --> 00:04:43,280
<i>Oppa!</i>

36
00:04:43,360 --> 00:04:44,960
This is <i>maekju</i>. This is chicken.

37
00:04:47,000 --> 00:04:49,800
<i>Daebak.</i> Amazing, <i>oppa</i>.

38
00:04:50,880 --> 00:04:52,640
Hellfire Cocktail,

39
00:04:53,440 --> 00:04:55,360
our signature.

40
00:04:57,920 --> 00:04:59,640
Then… <i>jjan</i>!

41
00:04:59,720 --> 00:05:01,360
<i>Jjan.</i>

42
00:05:01,440 --> 00:05:02,320
<i>Jjan</i> what?

43
00:05:02,400 --> 00:05:04,520
- It means cheers.
- Oh, it means cheers?

44
00:05:04,600 --> 00:05:06,280
Then <i>jjan</i>!

45
00:05:11,840 --> 00:05:14,200
Ms. Yong, can you dance?

46
00:05:14,960 --> 00:05:16,160
- A little.
- Just a little?

47
00:05:16,240 --> 00:05:17,320
Can I see?

48
00:05:20,920 --> 00:05:21,880
How do you dance?

49
00:05:23,880 --> 00:05:24,840
If you're doing this…

50
00:05:26,640 --> 00:05:27,520
Let's go.

51
00:05:28,960 --> 00:05:30,480
Change the move.

52
00:05:34,960 --> 00:05:36,000
Chew your chicken first.

53
00:05:41,720 --> 00:05:42,600
Alright.

54
00:05:46,200 --> 00:05:47,240
Did you finish your chicken?

55
00:05:47,320 --> 00:05:48,120
MAYSA

56
00:05:48,200 --> 00:05:49,160
Let's go.

57
00:05:52,200 --> 00:05:53,920
Hold my hand. Hold my hand.

58
00:05:54,000 --> 00:05:58,080
<i>Welcome to the callback service…</i>

59
00:06:06,760 --> 00:06:08,880
Come on, bro.

60
00:06:08,960 --> 00:06:10,640
Let's do this.

61
00:06:10,720 --> 00:06:11,720
Come on.

62
00:06:11,800 --> 00:06:13,280
Yeah.

63
00:06:13,360 --> 00:06:14,440
Yeah.

64
00:06:15,160 --> 00:06:17,160
This move.

65
00:06:19,360 --> 00:06:21,840
That's not enough, Ms. Fahsai.

66
00:06:21,920 --> 00:06:24,280
Pull the star like this.

67
00:06:24,360 --> 00:06:27,360
Try this.

68
00:06:27,440 --> 00:06:28,760
How?

69
00:06:28,840 --> 00:06:30,000
Like this.

70
00:06:30,080 --> 00:06:31,800
- Is it there?
- The star is there.

71
00:06:31,880 --> 00:06:33,160
Pull it.

72
00:06:34,080 --> 00:06:35,040
Yeah.

73
00:06:35,120 --> 00:06:36,960
Pull it.

74
00:06:37,960 --> 00:06:40,800
Come on. Pull it.

75
00:06:43,600 --> 00:06:45,680
The star is here now.

76
00:06:47,920 --> 00:06:49,480
Who do you give it to?

77
00:06:50,960 --> 00:06:52,640
She gives him the star.

78
00:06:57,240 --> 00:07:00,520
She gives him the star!

79
00:07:03,600 --> 00:07:05,160
He kept it for himself.

80
00:07:07,640 --> 00:07:09,960
What's next, Ms. Yong?

81
00:07:11,400 --> 00:07:12,480
Ms. Yong.

82
00:08:41,760 --> 00:08:42,720
Hello.

83
00:09:01,240 --> 00:09:03,800
Thank you. Excuse us.

84
00:09:33,120 --> 00:09:35,680
Looks like someone's
getting their heart broken tonight.

85
00:09:36,200 --> 00:09:37,520
Probably her.

86
00:09:58,280 --> 00:10:00,360
Are you playing games with me?

87
00:10:00,960 --> 00:10:04,800
Yesterday when you called,
I was with Fahsai.

88
00:10:05,520 --> 00:10:06,920
I couldn't move.

89
00:10:08,720 --> 00:10:12,320
You couldn't even call or text?

90
00:10:15,120 --> 00:10:16,200
I could.

91
00:10:17,680 --> 00:10:18,600
But…

92
00:10:21,920 --> 00:10:22,880
I was afraid.

93
00:10:24,160 --> 00:10:26,120
The more I talk to you,

94
00:10:28,160 --> 00:10:29,080
the more it hurts.

95
00:10:35,400 --> 00:10:36,960
You know why.

96
00:10:39,800 --> 00:10:43,040
Because we're the same kind of people.

97
00:10:56,600 --> 00:10:57,680
You said…

98
00:10:59,920 --> 00:11:01,600
your destination is Samut.

99
00:11:04,080 --> 00:11:05,040
And mine…

100
00:11:08,440 --> 00:11:10,640
ends with Fahsai.

101
00:12:03,680 --> 00:12:04,920
But my heart…

102
00:12:09,800 --> 00:12:10,840
is here.

103
00:12:15,800 --> 00:12:19,000
V? What does it stand for?

104
00:12:19,080 --> 00:12:22,360
Victory… for others.

105
00:12:25,120 --> 00:12:26,560
But for us…

106
00:12:30,160 --> 00:12:31,680
it means…

107
00:12:35,320 --> 00:12:36,920
my heart is with you.

108
00:12:41,120 --> 00:12:43,280
I'm not just taking your heart.

109
00:12:44,480 --> 00:12:47,080
I want all of you.

110
00:12:49,400 --> 00:12:51,320
So we can have more fun together.

111
00:13:11,480 --> 00:13:13,640
Prapai. Ms. Prapai.

112
00:13:14,160 --> 00:13:17,320
You were just going to walk in without me?

113
00:13:18,400 --> 00:13:21,440
Look at this. There's a whole line
of girls waiting to walk in with me.

114
00:13:22,120 --> 00:13:23,920
The line goes all the way
to the hotel entrance.

115
00:13:24,000 --> 00:13:25,280
Hey.

116
00:13:25,360 --> 00:13:28,160
I'm not in the mood
to listen to you brag right now.

117
00:13:29,160 --> 00:13:31,080
Why so serious?

118
00:13:33,440 --> 00:13:35,160
Look.

119
00:13:35,240 --> 00:13:38,120
There's a handsome guy
right here offering his arm.

120
00:13:38,200 --> 00:13:41,920
If you don't take it,
other girls will think

121
00:13:42,680 --> 00:13:43,640
you're not very smart.

122
00:13:46,160 --> 00:13:49,560
Don't forget why you came today.

123
00:13:50,920 --> 00:13:52,400
You came for your brother.

124
00:13:57,080 --> 00:13:58,800
For your brother.

125
00:14:06,240 --> 00:14:08,600
Come on. Let's go take some photos.

126
00:14:09,640 --> 00:14:10,880
Let's go.

127
00:14:36,520 --> 00:14:38,040
I went into the wrong room.

128
00:14:38,120 --> 00:14:39,400
I meant to find you,

129
00:14:40,280 --> 00:14:41,400
but I ran into Mr. Wayu.

130
00:14:42,880 --> 00:14:44,680
Why are you two in separate rooms?

131
00:14:44,760 --> 00:14:47,240
So I got to see the groom
before the bride.

132
00:14:50,920 --> 00:14:52,920
It doesn't matter who sees him first.

133
00:14:53,920 --> 00:14:56,760
From now on,
I'll be seeing Wayu every day anyway.

134
00:15:03,600 --> 00:15:04,960
You look beautiful.

135
00:15:07,400 --> 00:15:08,400
Thank you.

136
00:15:18,400 --> 00:15:20,520
That dress really suits you, Fahsai.

137
00:15:21,160 --> 00:15:24,160
I'm honestly jealous.

138
00:15:37,920 --> 00:15:38,880
Let's go.

139
00:15:40,240 --> 00:15:41,240
Okay.

140
00:16:09,320 --> 00:16:10,400
Where have you been?

141
00:16:13,040 --> 00:16:15,560
Why'd you leave Samut drinking alone?

142
00:16:18,080 --> 00:16:19,520
That's exactly why

143
00:16:20,200 --> 00:16:22,560
Samut hasn't proposed to you.

144
00:16:24,400 --> 00:16:25,920
Even Wayu, who came later,

145
00:16:26,000 --> 00:16:29,000
managed to marry Fahsai before you.

146
00:16:29,680 --> 00:16:31,280
Because he's smarter than you.

147
00:16:34,680 --> 00:16:38,920
Then again, maybe Fahsai
is more naive than her brother.

148
00:16:39,640 --> 00:16:41,560
Maybe she's being tricked.

149
00:16:41,640 --> 00:16:45,160
Maybe Wayu's marrying her
just for business.

150
00:16:47,000 --> 00:16:48,560
That's even better.

151
00:16:50,000 --> 00:16:53,080
Samut will finally stop
obsessing over his sister.

152
00:17:00,160 --> 00:17:02,080
You chose this path.

153
00:17:02,960 --> 00:17:05,079
Don't let anything shake you.

154
00:17:06,800 --> 00:17:08,680
Right now, you need to prove

155
00:17:08,760 --> 00:17:11,240
that you're the most
suitable one for Samut.

156
00:17:12,839 --> 00:17:14,200
Go back to him now.

157
00:17:15,839 --> 00:17:16,920
Is there a problem?

158
00:17:21,480 --> 00:17:22,440
Are you guests?

159
00:17:24,920 --> 00:17:28,359
It's the minister's daughter's wedding.
We need to keep everything secure.

160
00:17:29,720 --> 00:17:30,600
What's going on?

161
00:17:31,120 --> 00:17:32,720
These two look suspicious, sir.

162
00:17:33,240 --> 00:17:34,640
Did you get it?

163
00:17:37,640 --> 00:17:40,680
Did you get the photo yet?
I told you to take a picture of May.

164
00:17:43,400 --> 00:17:44,600
What's going on?

165
00:17:46,360 --> 00:17:49,200
Oh! May!

166
00:17:49,280 --> 00:17:50,360
There you are!

167
00:17:50,440 --> 00:17:53,120
I'm such a big fan of your dramas.

168
00:17:53,200 --> 00:17:55,280
I've watched everything.

169
00:17:55,360 --> 00:17:57,560
Can I take a photo with you?

170
00:17:58,320 --> 00:18:00,240
- Sure.
- Thank you.

171
00:18:01,720 --> 00:18:03,480
Guys, come take the photo for me.

172
00:18:03,560 --> 00:18:05,680
Hurry. Don't keep May waiting.

173
00:18:05,760 --> 00:18:06,720
Excuse me, May.

174
00:18:06,800 --> 00:18:08,520
- Thank you.
- Sure.

175
00:18:09,840 --> 00:18:10,880
Alright.

176
00:18:11,720 --> 00:18:13,520
One, two, three.

177
00:18:13,600 --> 00:18:14,440
Good.

178
00:18:15,160 --> 00:18:17,040
- One more, please.
- I want a picture too.

179
00:18:17,560 --> 00:18:18,360
Hurry up.

180
00:18:18,440 --> 00:18:20,000
One more, please.

181
00:18:20,080 --> 00:18:21,640
Minister Rakchart is looking for you.

182
00:18:22,600 --> 00:18:24,800
One, two, three.

183
00:18:26,480 --> 00:18:29,720
That was close. We need
to be more careful from now on.

184
00:18:29,800 --> 00:18:32,480
Why did you take so many photos?
I'm too lazy to delete them all.

185
00:18:34,000 --> 00:18:36,320
Weren't you May's fan?

186
00:18:38,120 --> 00:18:40,680
Still, it wasn't a wasted trip.

187
00:18:40,760 --> 00:18:43,800
At least we found out politicians and cops

188
00:18:43,880 --> 00:18:46,160
are basically two peas in a rotten pod.

189
00:18:46,240 --> 00:18:47,320
Exactly.

190
00:18:47,840 --> 00:18:49,720
They really should stick together.

191
00:18:49,800 --> 00:18:52,760
Might as well exchange sons and daughters.

192
00:18:56,040 --> 00:18:58,760
Captain, these are employees
at Wayu's spicy salad restaurant.

193
00:18:59,640 --> 00:19:01,640
Praya, Sam, Phupa,

194
00:19:01,720 --> 00:19:02,960
and Pud.

195
00:19:03,720 --> 00:19:05,840
Hello. I'm Captain Anawin.

196
00:19:08,160 --> 00:19:09,440
Let's find something to drink.

197
00:19:15,640 --> 00:19:16,880
Come on, everyone.

198
00:19:18,160 --> 00:19:19,760
Nice to meet you.

199
00:19:19,840 --> 00:19:20,960
Thank you.

200
00:19:21,040 --> 00:19:22,120
Bottoms up?

201
00:19:23,080 --> 00:19:24,080
We'd better not.

202
00:19:25,400 --> 00:19:27,440
As the bride's father,

203
00:19:28,760 --> 00:19:31,080
today I feel both happy

204
00:19:32,160 --> 00:19:34,080
and deeply emotional.

205
00:19:36,880 --> 00:19:39,600
I now give my beloved daughter

206
00:19:40,800 --> 00:19:42,240
to the groom,

207
00:19:43,840 --> 00:19:45,280
Wayu Buranachat,

208
00:19:46,520 --> 00:19:49,480
a man who has proven himself

209
00:19:49,560 --> 00:19:51,480
to be visionary

210
00:19:52,640 --> 00:19:55,200
and capable of protecting my daughter.

211
00:20:07,760 --> 00:20:09,880
May I invite all our honored guests

212
00:20:09,960 --> 00:20:12,440
to raise your glasses
and bless the bride and groom.

213
00:20:12,960 --> 00:20:14,640
- Cheers!
- Cheers!

214
00:20:14,720 --> 00:20:16,360
- Cheers!
- Cheers!

215
00:20:16,440 --> 00:20:18,720
- Cheers!
- Cheers!

216
00:20:31,400 --> 00:20:34,600
After the toast, kiss! Kiss!

217
00:20:36,400 --> 00:20:37,920
Yeah, kiss, kiss.

218
00:20:38,520 --> 00:20:40,160
Kiss! Kiss!

219
00:20:40,240 --> 00:20:42,200
Kiss! Kiss!

220
00:20:42,280 --> 00:20:45,640
Kiss! Kiss!

221
00:20:45,720 --> 00:20:50,000
Kiss! Kiss!

222
00:20:50,080 --> 00:20:52,760
Kiss! Kiss!

223
00:20:52,840 --> 00:20:56,080
Kiss! Kiss!

224
00:20:56,160 --> 00:20:58,760
Kiss! Kiss!

225
00:20:58,840 --> 00:21:02,160
Kiss! Kiss!

226
00:21:22,040 --> 00:21:22,920
Prapai.

227
00:21:24,480 --> 00:21:25,680
Prapai.

228
00:21:25,760 --> 00:21:28,880
Where are you going?
The wedding isn't over yet.

229
00:21:28,960 --> 00:21:32,560
You expect me to stand there and watch
Wayu kiss that woman until the end?

230
00:21:39,440 --> 00:21:41,400
I shouldn't have come.

231
00:21:48,160 --> 00:21:49,800
But you did great.

232
00:21:51,800 --> 00:21:52,720
Great how?

233
00:21:53,240 --> 00:21:57,000
You came for your brother. And you did it.

234
00:21:57,840 --> 00:21:59,280
You did really well.

235
00:22:08,600 --> 00:22:09,880
Don't cry.

236
00:22:29,560 --> 00:22:31,440
Were you mocking me?

237
00:22:34,360 --> 00:22:38,480
You think you can fool my father
and my sister and get away with anything?

238
00:22:39,800 --> 00:22:40,920
You have no right

239
00:22:41,440 --> 00:22:43,240
to touch my sister!

240
00:22:43,320 --> 00:22:44,640
No right?

241
00:22:46,000 --> 00:22:47,280
What do you mean no right?

242
00:22:48,000 --> 00:22:51,040
The groom kissing the bride,
what's wrong with that?

243
00:22:53,800 --> 00:22:56,480
You think I wouldn't dare?

244
00:22:59,200 --> 00:23:02,920
I've killed people before
and never gone to jail.

245
00:23:03,760 --> 00:23:05,160
Even if it's you.

246
00:23:06,520 --> 00:23:07,560
You want to try?

247
00:23:10,640 --> 00:23:11,560
Damn it.

248
00:23:12,760 --> 00:23:15,040
Fahsai will never know

249
00:23:15,680 --> 00:23:18,760
why her groom suddenly disappeared.

250
00:23:21,360 --> 00:23:23,000
Are you done settling things?

251
00:23:33,360 --> 00:23:35,920
I'd like my groom back, please.

252
00:23:58,480 --> 00:24:00,960
Careful. We're almost at the bed.

253
00:24:01,040 --> 00:24:02,680
Sit, sit.

254
00:24:10,400 --> 00:24:11,520
Here.

255
00:24:11,600 --> 00:24:12,760
I'll leave your bag here.

256
00:24:18,480 --> 00:24:20,320
Poppy.

257
00:24:20,400 --> 00:24:22,240
Mommy's baby.

258
00:24:22,320 --> 00:24:25,600
Come here. Let mommy kiss you.

259
00:24:25,680 --> 00:24:26,840
Whoa, easy!

260
00:24:28,080 --> 00:24:28,920
Don't throw up here.

261
00:24:29,000 --> 00:24:30,000
Go to the bathroom.

262
00:24:49,960 --> 00:24:50,800
So comfy.

263
00:24:57,800 --> 00:25:00,480
Thank you, my child,
for making this decision.

264
00:25:01,800 --> 00:25:03,320
Now I can stop worrying.

265
00:25:03,400 --> 00:25:06,160
The plan can move forward.

266
00:25:06,240 --> 00:25:08,080
I just don't want to go abroad.

267
00:25:08,960 --> 00:25:10,160
I want to stay with you.

268
00:25:12,800 --> 00:25:15,680
You're such a sweet talker.

269
00:25:19,240 --> 00:25:20,560
Take good care of Fahsai.

270
00:25:21,360 --> 00:25:23,120
Don't disappoint me.

271
00:25:28,400 --> 00:25:30,560
I'll take the best care of her.

272
00:26:05,040 --> 00:26:07,280
The room next door is ready.
You can rest there.

273
00:26:22,040 --> 00:26:23,360
On the wedding night,

274
00:26:24,040 --> 00:26:26,200
you're sending the groom to another room?

275
00:26:30,120 --> 00:26:31,000
Hey!

276
00:26:31,920 --> 00:26:32,760
Hey.

277
00:26:57,280 --> 00:26:58,320
Hey.

278
00:26:58,840 --> 00:27:01,320
Your brother has eyes and ears everywhere.

279
00:27:02,360 --> 00:27:05,400
But you said you checked,

280
00:27:05,480 --> 00:27:07,000
and there are no cameras,
no tracking devices.

281
00:27:07,080 --> 00:27:09,360
He placed people all around the house.

282
00:27:09,440 --> 00:27:11,800
Upstairs, downstairs, outside.

283
00:27:12,360 --> 00:27:13,760
We can't let anyone get suspicious.

284
00:27:15,480 --> 00:27:16,520
What do you mean?

285
00:27:16,600 --> 00:27:18,200
You don't have to do anything.

286
00:27:21,240 --> 00:27:22,360
I'll handle it.

287
00:28:06,680 --> 00:28:08,400
You're up so early, darling.

288
00:28:10,160 --> 00:28:11,400
Sleep a bit more.

289
00:28:14,640 --> 00:28:19,080
I'm going to check on breakfast.

290
00:28:28,360 --> 00:28:29,960
I'm so lucky.

291
00:28:32,200 --> 00:28:33,680
I'm starting to envy myself.

292
00:28:35,640 --> 00:28:37,480
I have such a caring wife.

293
00:28:39,560 --> 00:28:40,400
You're…

294
00:28:56,760 --> 00:28:58,960
Here!

295
00:28:59,960 --> 00:29:03,320
I'll go check on breakfast now.

296
00:29:20,040 --> 00:29:23,400
Fahsai, why are you blushing?

297
00:29:59,560 --> 00:30:00,640
Did you rape me?

298
00:30:00,720 --> 00:30:01,720
Rape?!

299
00:30:01,800 --> 00:30:03,760
- You're the worst!
- Stop. Wait.

300
00:30:03,840 --> 00:30:05,760
Calm down!

301
00:30:05,840 --> 00:30:08,080
Look at the situation. Who's raping who?

302
00:30:15,920 --> 00:30:19,440
Hey. You want to know
what happened last night?

303
00:30:21,560 --> 00:30:24,520
You were wasted and refused to go home.

304
00:30:24,600 --> 00:30:26,640
Just getting you here

305
00:30:26,720 --> 00:30:30,480
and waiting for you to pass out
nearly killed me.

306
00:30:30,560 --> 00:30:32,240
Who'd have the energy
to do anything to you?

307
00:30:32,320 --> 00:30:36,040
And even if I did, I wouldn't.

308
00:30:36,720 --> 00:30:38,000
You know why?

309
00:30:38,600 --> 00:30:42,440
You're not my type at all.

310
00:30:44,600 --> 00:30:47,480
Then where are my clothes?

311
00:30:48,600 --> 00:30:51,080
There. See?

312
00:30:55,320 --> 00:30:56,480
Turn around.

313
00:30:57,600 --> 00:30:59,400
Wait. What are you doing?

314
00:31:00,120 --> 00:31:01,440
You really didn't do anything, right?

315
00:31:01,520 --> 00:31:03,400
You were the one all over me.

316
00:31:05,400 --> 00:31:07,840
Think about it. I was lying on the floor.

317
00:31:07,920 --> 00:31:12,200
You were on the bed,
and you still slid down onto my chest.

318
00:31:13,640 --> 00:31:15,880
Who knows what you did to me.

319
00:31:15,960 --> 00:31:17,840
It's my loss.

320
00:31:18,360 --> 00:31:20,160
Give me compensation.

321
00:31:20,920 --> 00:31:22,200
Come on. You're so rich, aren't you?

322
00:31:22,280 --> 00:31:23,880
You idiot!

323
00:31:31,920 --> 00:31:33,360
Good morning, Dad.

324
00:31:33,440 --> 00:31:34,600
Oh.

325
00:31:35,160 --> 00:31:37,920
You could've slept in.

326
00:31:38,000 --> 00:31:40,000
You must've been exhausted last night.

327
00:31:40,520 --> 00:31:43,720
Fahsai is probably excited
about the honeymoon.

328
00:31:44,840 --> 00:31:48,880
With the election coming,
Fahsai needs to help with party work.

329
00:31:49,960 --> 00:31:53,040
Otherwise, I'd send you to Europe.

330
00:31:53,800 --> 00:31:55,560
Traveling domestically is fine enough.

331
00:31:55,640 --> 00:31:57,680
Less travel, more rest.

332
00:32:03,600 --> 00:32:05,160
Bring the food.

333
00:32:16,440 --> 00:32:17,600
Here.

334
00:32:18,200 --> 00:32:19,280
I'll serve you.

335
00:32:19,360 --> 00:32:21,080
- I can do it myself.
- Don't be stubborn.

336
00:32:25,800 --> 00:32:26,680
Here.

337
00:32:28,440 --> 00:32:29,520
How much?

338
00:32:31,080 --> 00:32:33,200
- That's enough.
- I haven't even served you yet.

339
00:32:39,680 --> 00:32:41,920
Good thing there was a market nearby.

340
00:32:42,000 --> 00:32:44,520
Otherwise, you'd be going home
in your underwear.

341
00:32:49,200 --> 00:32:51,200
No need to sneak. Just take it.

342
00:32:57,640 --> 00:32:59,440
Is this the Jaiaree case?

343
00:33:00,040 --> 00:33:03,520
Since you already know, help me out.

344
00:33:04,680 --> 00:33:05,960
So,

345
00:33:07,240 --> 00:33:10,680
the neighbor witness moved abroad.

346
00:33:12,080 --> 00:33:15,240
And the DNA from the tooth
the undertaker gave us…

347
00:33:16,640 --> 00:33:17,480
it's not Peeraka's.

348
00:33:21,680 --> 00:33:23,440
Why don't you look surprised at all?

349
00:33:25,840 --> 00:33:27,160
I'm so surprised!

350
00:33:28,120 --> 00:33:29,320
Well…

351
00:33:29,400 --> 00:33:33,520
I must be hungover. I have a headache.

352
00:33:40,000 --> 00:33:42,960
So, apart from Aemika,

353
00:33:43,840 --> 00:33:45,600
we don't have any other witnesses?

354
00:33:54,320 --> 00:33:55,760
You sure it's here, Sam?

355
00:34:11,320 --> 00:34:13,120
Be careful.

356
00:34:15,400 --> 00:34:17,040
Should I get that dry-cleaned for you?

357
00:34:17,120 --> 00:34:18,199
It's fine.

358
00:34:18,280 --> 00:34:19,480
What did you do to her?

359
00:34:21,120 --> 00:34:23,360
Praya, stop!

360
00:34:24,360 --> 00:34:25,679
How could you do this?

361
00:34:28,360 --> 00:34:29,800
Praya.

362
00:34:29,880 --> 00:34:30,800
Stop!

363
00:34:30,880 --> 00:34:31,960
- Listen first!
- Stop!

364
00:34:32,040 --> 00:34:33,320
What's wrong with you?

365
00:34:34,040 --> 00:34:37,000
I came here with him.
You have no right to hurt him like this.

366
00:34:37,080 --> 00:34:39,239
But the boss told me to protect you.

367
00:34:39,320 --> 00:34:40,600
Did he drug you?

368
00:34:41,920 --> 00:34:43,159
I'm not a child.

369
00:34:43,239 --> 00:34:45,840
I know who I can trust and who I can't.

370
00:34:49,679 --> 00:34:50,840
Just go back.

371
00:35:03,440 --> 00:35:04,800
Let's go.

372
00:36:03,880 --> 00:36:05,000
It's so beautiful.

373
00:36:07,480 --> 00:36:08,800
You want to take a nap?

374
00:36:10,480 --> 00:36:12,600
You probably didn't get
much sleep last night.

375
00:36:15,400 --> 00:36:16,600
You don't have to do anything.

376
00:36:19,640 --> 00:36:20,840
I'll handle it.

377
00:36:45,280 --> 00:36:47,800
Hey. We're just
in a fake marriage, you know.

378
00:36:49,040 --> 00:36:50,800
Why turn it on?
People might get suspicious.

379
00:36:50,880 --> 00:36:53,680
I'm not some naïve girl
who believes everything you say.

380
00:36:53,760 --> 00:36:56,440
If people don't believe we're a couple
because the lights are on, let them.

381
00:36:56,520 --> 00:36:57,880
You're really stubborn.

382
00:36:57,960 --> 00:36:59,320
I'm not stubborn.

383
00:37:00,360 --> 00:37:02,520
I feel sticky, and I'm going to shower.

384
00:37:02,600 --> 00:37:04,840
If you don't want to sleep in this room
or on the floor,

385
00:37:04,920 --> 00:37:07,000
you should go shower too.

386
00:37:09,480 --> 00:37:12,800
You want to sleep with the lights on,
all fresh and cuddling?

387
00:37:13,640 --> 00:37:14,680
No.

388
00:37:15,200 --> 00:37:17,680
Just don't forget our agreement.

389
00:37:18,720 --> 00:37:21,160
This is just a fake marriage.

390
00:37:22,400 --> 00:37:25,920
If you want to sleep on the bed,
I'll put a pillow barrier down,

391
00:37:26,000 --> 00:37:28,400
and you are not allowed to cross it.

392
00:37:29,600 --> 00:37:31,200
If I really wanted to do something,

393
00:37:31,960 --> 00:37:34,760
do you think a few inches of pillow
would stop me?

394
00:37:36,240 --> 00:37:39,560
I could push it aside with one finger.

395
00:37:42,800 --> 00:37:46,320
A ten-inch pillow
can be as strong as the Great Wall

396
00:37:47,120 --> 00:37:49,440
if you keep your word
and have enough honor.

397
00:37:51,320 --> 00:37:54,360
I heard your father was a mafia boss,

398
00:37:55,000 --> 00:37:58,200
but he was also a gentleman with pride.

399
00:37:59,880 --> 00:38:02,800
His son shouldn't be any different, right?

400
00:38:17,760 --> 00:38:21,120
Still, thank you for keeping your word.

401
00:38:23,920 --> 00:38:27,440
But over the next couple of days
we're here, who knows?

402
00:38:29,120 --> 00:38:30,880
I might tear up the contract.

403
00:38:35,480 --> 00:38:36,920
Tear it up?

404
00:38:55,600 --> 00:38:57,400
What do you want me to check?

405
00:38:57,480 --> 00:39:00,520
Please hurry. The maid might come.

406
00:39:01,240 --> 00:39:02,720
What's the room like?

407
00:39:04,000 --> 00:39:06,000
How should I even report this?

408
00:39:06,680 --> 00:39:09,760
Just say what you see.

409
00:39:10,360 --> 00:39:12,800
The bed sheets and blankets
are all crumpled.

410
00:39:12,880 --> 00:39:15,280
<i>And the sofa</i>

411
00:39:15,360 --> 00:39:17,320
<i>and pillows are everywhere.</i>

412
00:39:17,400 --> 00:39:20,480
No way they just lay there and talked.

413
00:39:20,560 --> 00:39:22,680
It must've been intense.

414
00:39:24,760 --> 00:39:28,400
I'd say at least two or three rounds.

415
00:39:29,120 --> 00:39:30,120
Stop it.

416
00:39:30,640 --> 00:39:32,200
But, Mr. Samut,

417
00:39:32,280 --> 00:39:34,120
you asked me to report it.

418
00:39:34,200 --> 00:39:35,880
I said stop it!

419
00:39:42,920 --> 00:39:44,080
Serves you right.

420
00:39:53,120 --> 00:39:54,400
Who's that?

421
00:39:56,520 --> 00:39:57,600
Someone says

422
00:39:58,120 --> 00:40:01,280
they have a secret about MP Mahasamut
to be exposed.

423
00:40:05,000 --> 00:40:06,120
Who's "someone"?

424
00:40:08,800 --> 00:40:09,840
And…

425
00:40:16,040 --> 00:40:18,080
How do you read that?

426
00:40:19,520 --> 00:40:20,680
It means an unidentified person.

427
00:40:23,280 --> 00:40:25,120
Anonymous…

428
00:40:26,040 --> 00:40:27,240
A secret?

429
00:40:29,400 --> 00:40:30,240
What kind of secret?

430
00:40:37,080 --> 00:40:40,600
They say they have evidence
to take Samut down.

431
00:40:41,400 --> 00:40:42,600
Sounds interesting.

432
00:40:43,320 --> 00:40:44,960
<i>Our page is about</i>

433
00:40:45,040 --> 00:40:47,720
exposing corrupt people.

434
00:40:47,800 --> 00:40:49,080
We can't ignore this.

435
00:40:49,160 --> 00:40:50,360
But it's risky.

436
00:40:50,440 --> 00:40:52,720
They won't reveal themselves.

437
00:40:52,800 --> 00:40:54,880
<i>How do we know it's not a trap?</i>

438
00:40:54,960 --> 00:40:57,840
But if we don't go, we'll never know.

439
00:40:58,880 --> 00:41:01,000
They might really have something big.

440
00:41:01,080 --> 00:41:02,960
If you really want to go…

441
00:41:03,040 --> 00:41:04,320
<i>We'll be careful.</i>

442
00:41:04,400 --> 00:41:06,200
I'll take care of everyone.

443
00:41:06,280 --> 00:41:07,760
Then listen.

444
00:41:09,560 --> 00:41:11,080
No matter how important
the information is,

445
00:41:12,760 --> 00:41:14,480
your lives come first.

446
00:41:14,560 --> 00:41:16,440
<i>Make sure you come back safe.</i>

447
00:41:18,160 --> 00:41:20,720
Now that's more like it.

448
00:41:22,840 --> 00:41:26,000
Don't worry, we'll be fine.

449
00:42:04,840 --> 00:42:06,120
Have something for me?

450
00:42:07,960 --> 00:42:10,280
I've got feelings. You want them?

451
00:42:12,040 --> 00:42:13,200
Nonsense.

452
00:42:23,280 --> 00:42:24,480
Let's go to dinner. I'm hungry.

453
00:42:30,760 --> 00:42:31,760
Please.

454
00:42:32,280 --> 00:42:33,440
Thank you.

455
00:43:10,600 --> 00:43:12,600
Sometimes I ask myself…

456
00:43:14,720 --> 00:43:17,040
why I have to put myself through this.

457
00:43:19,800 --> 00:43:23,800
You mean marrying me
and lying to everyone?

458
00:43:25,760 --> 00:43:26,600
Yes.

459
00:43:40,960 --> 00:43:44,360
Why don't we just make it real?

460
00:43:46,240 --> 00:43:49,320
Like couples who fall in love
and get married.

461
00:43:54,280 --> 00:43:55,560
Talking nonsense again.

462
00:43:59,720 --> 00:44:01,160
Or are you going to deny

463
00:44:05,160 --> 00:44:07,120
that you feel nothing for me?

464
00:44:29,560 --> 00:44:30,480
Wait.

465
00:44:33,320 --> 00:44:37,160
If you're about to tie my hair
like some drama lead…

466
00:44:40,200 --> 00:44:41,080
no need.

467
00:44:41,600 --> 00:44:43,360
I can do it myself.

468
00:45:00,560 --> 00:45:01,760
Done.

469
00:45:04,200 --> 00:45:07,040
Beautiful, but it can be even better.

470
00:45:59,280 --> 00:46:00,280
Hey.

471
00:46:01,040 --> 00:46:02,080
You're going to pick up?

472
00:46:03,040 --> 00:46:05,400
Samut might have something urgent.

473
00:46:07,760 --> 00:46:10,120
He just wants to ruin our honeymoon.

474
00:46:10,920 --> 00:46:12,160
He might even

475
00:46:12,240 --> 00:46:14,760
have people watching us.

476
00:46:19,480 --> 00:46:23,480
You need everyone to believe
this is a real honeymoon.

477
00:46:24,720 --> 00:46:26,400
If you want our plan to work,

478
00:46:27,120 --> 00:46:28,600
you can't be distracted by anyone else.

479
00:46:29,280 --> 00:46:31,720
This is just us.

480
00:46:37,800 --> 00:46:39,240
Do we really have to go this far?

481
00:46:42,000 --> 00:46:45,560
Yeah, so for now, just stay close to me.

482
00:46:50,680 --> 00:46:51,520
Give it back.

483
00:46:52,640 --> 00:46:54,720
Hey. Hey.

484
00:46:54,800 --> 00:46:55,760
Hey.

485
00:46:56,280 --> 00:46:57,520
Hey.

486
00:46:57,600 --> 00:46:58,640
Hey.

487
00:47:00,240 --> 00:47:01,320
Hey.

488
00:47:23,600 --> 00:47:25,160
You still want it?

489
00:47:34,560 --> 00:47:37,240
I'm only going along with this
for the honeymoon. Just two days.

490
00:47:42,840 --> 00:47:45,880
<i>Welcome to the callback service.</i>

491
00:47:45,960 --> 00:47:47,480
What's gotten into you?

492
00:47:47,560 --> 00:47:51,160
You know your sister's on her honeymoon.

493
00:47:52,040 --> 00:47:55,640
She might want to spend time alone
with her husband.

494
00:47:57,520 --> 00:48:01,600
Picking up a call wouldn't ruin anything.

495
00:48:04,840 --> 00:48:06,200
It's Wayu.

496
00:48:07,400 --> 00:48:09,040
He's the one stopping her.

497
00:48:12,480 --> 00:48:15,240
You still can't accept him
as your brother-in-law?

498
00:48:16,240 --> 00:48:19,720
They're already married.

499
00:48:20,360 --> 00:48:22,240
They're officially husband and wife.

500
00:48:23,520 --> 00:48:28,040
I think you should
focus on bigger things.

501
00:48:28,120 --> 00:48:29,320
The election is coming.

502
00:48:35,560 --> 00:48:39,040
I'm only saying this because I care.

503
00:49:43,280 --> 00:49:44,640
The guests have arrived, sir.

504
00:49:58,160 --> 00:49:59,200
I admit it.

505
00:49:59,720 --> 00:50:01,280
I did sleep with that woman.

506
00:50:02,320 --> 00:50:04,280
But it was consensual.

507
00:50:05,680 --> 00:50:07,680
I didn't force her like the news says.

508
00:50:09,000 --> 00:50:10,920
They arranged everything for me.

509
00:50:11,000 --> 00:50:12,400
They?

510
00:50:13,200 --> 00:50:14,040
Heaven Club.

511
00:50:15,400 --> 00:50:16,640
So you're saying Mahasamut

512
00:50:16,720 --> 00:50:19,200
arranged the service

513
00:50:19,760 --> 00:50:21,120
and then exposed you?

514
00:50:21,200 --> 00:50:23,440
That night, I didn't
want to go to the club.

515
00:50:23,520 --> 00:50:24,840
It would be bad for my image.

516
00:50:25,440 --> 00:50:27,000
So they arranged it at a hotel instead.

517
00:50:28,760 --> 00:50:31,440
If it wasn't him, who would it be?

518
00:50:32,360 --> 00:50:33,600
Who else would have that video?

519
00:50:34,680 --> 00:50:36,680
Who else knew I was there that night?

520
00:50:37,880 --> 00:50:41,000
He betrayed me
and destroyed my reputation.

521
00:50:41,080 --> 00:50:42,440
How do we know

522
00:50:43,040 --> 00:50:46,000
you're telling the truth?

523
00:50:46,600 --> 00:50:48,880
You think I'd destroy myself
a second time?

524
00:50:50,160 --> 00:50:52,240
I'm showing my face, talking to you,

525
00:50:52,760 --> 00:50:54,640
when I don't even know who you are.

526
00:50:56,000 --> 00:50:57,560
You don't need to know who we are.

527
00:50:58,600 --> 00:51:00,120
Just know you can trust us.

528
00:51:00,800 --> 00:51:02,480
But the question is, can we trust you?

529
00:51:02,560 --> 00:51:04,080
Tomorrow at 11 p.m.,

530
00:51:05,040 --> 00:51:07,440
a female celebrity will be lured
into providing services there.

531
00:51:13,400 --> 00:51:14,640
If you dare to verify it,

532
00:51:15,880 --> 00:51:18,480
you'll know whether I can be trusted.

533
00:51:22,480 --> 00:51:25,920
I'm betting what's left
of my reputation and honor on this.

534
00:51:30,600 --> 00:51:31,640
Dharn?

535
00:51:32,160 --> 00:51:35,360
Surprised? We couldn't believe it either.

536
00:51:35,440 --> 00:51:37,920
He says Heaven Club betrayed him.

537
00:51:38,000 --> 00:51:40,280
Then he's probably looking for revenge.

538
00:51:43,000 --> 00:51:44,960
But how do we know

539
00:51:45,480 --> 00:51:47,040
he's not using us?

540
00:51:47,640 --> 00:51:50,040
He's putting his reputation on the line.

541
00:51:50,120 --> 00:51:52,720
And he already knows
we're the Mad Dog page.

542
00:51:52,800 --> 00:51:56,000
If he's lying, we'll expose him.
Tthere's no way he gets away with it.

543
00:51:56,880 --> 00:51:58,640
But you have a point.

544
00:51:59,160 --> 00:52:01,240
We still need more evidence.

545
00:52:02,480 --> 00:52:03,760
Handle your side first.

546
00:52:04,520 --> 00:52:07,200
I'll call you if anything comes up.

547
00:52:13,240 --> 00:52:16,520
Why didn't you tell him
about the lead Dharn gave us?

548
00:52:16,600 --> 00:52:18,720
I don't want Wayu worrying.

549
00:52:19,240 --> 00:52:21,600
If Fahsai or Rakchart notices,
they'll get suspicious too.

550
00:52:22,120 --> 00:52:24,760
So we're just going to do nothing?

551
00:52:24,840 --> 00:52:28,040
If what Dharn said is real,

552
00:52:28,120 --> 00:52:30,240
that woman is walking into hell.

553
00:52:31,200 --> 00:52:32,400
Exactly.

554
00:52:32,480 --> 00:52:34,720
We can save her

555
00:52:34,800 --> 00:52:37,200
and get evidence to take Samut down.

556
00:52:38,760 --> 00:52:40,800
We can tell Wayu after we succeed.

557
00:52:41,800 --> 00:52:43,800
He'll be proud of us.

558
00:52:44,320 --> 00:52:46,960
And if it's fake,

559
00:52:47,040 --> 00:52:49,920
we just walk out of that club.

560
00:52:50,000 --> 00:52:51,720
Easy.

561
00:52:52,640 --> 00:52:53,880
Right?

562
00:53:12,240 --> 00:53:13,200
Let's go out.

563
00:53:13,800 --> 00:53:15,040
It's way more fun than staying here.

564
00:53:16,920 --> 00:53:17,960
How much more fun?

565
00:53:19,360 --> 00:53:21,440
You'll be screaming, I guarantee it.

566
00:53:23,960 --> 00:53:26,400
No way I'd scream like crazy.

567
00:54:14,560 --> 00:54:16,880
That was so fun. What's next?

568
00:54:16,960 --> 00:54:19,080
- What's next?
- Is your throat okay?

569
00:54:21,680 --> 00:54:23,360
Come on, there's a better one.

570
00:54:31,960 --> 00:54:33,680
Whoever gets there first buys dinner.

571
00:54:33,760 --> 00:54:34,760
Really?

572
00:54:34,840 --> 00:54:36,560
If I say so, then yes.

573
00:54:38,120 --> 00:54:39,520
Yes, boss.

574
00:55:27,520 --> 00:55:29,520
I screamed my head off.

575
00:55:30,800 --> 00:55:34,680
It's been so long
since I had this much fun. Thank you.

576
00:55:36,240 --> 00:55:38,120
I told you you'd scream.

577
00:55:40,400 --> 00:55:42,240
Sometimes you screamed
even louder than me.

578
00:55:43,000 --> 00:55:45,640
Did you bring me here
because you knew I like water?

579
00:55:47,760 --> 00:55:51,040
Yes, but that's only half of it.

580
00:55:51,960 --> 00:55:53,800
I'm more selfish than that.

581
00:55:55,080 --> 00:55:56,400
Selfish?

582
00:55:57,080 --> 00:56:01,080
I brought you here
because I knew it'd be fun

583
00:56:02,080 --> 00:56:03,520
and you'd be happy

584
00:56:04,760 --> 00:56:05,840
And?

585
00:56:06,520 --> 00:56:10,320
And when you're happy, I'm happy too.

586
00:56:11,880 --> 00:56:14,960
When you smile and laugh,

587
00:56:17,320 --> 00:56:20,280
I feel really happy.

588
00:56:45,600 --> 00:56:49,800
Samut, don't forget tonight's party.

589
00:56:49,880 --> 00:56:53,120
I already told the station director
that you'd come.

590
00:57:23,600 --> 00:57:27,160
Yes? Did the outfit arrive?

591
00:57:27,240 --> 00:57:30,400
It did. But didn't you check?

592
00:57:30,480 --> 00:57:32,920
These earrings don't match.

593
00:57:33,000 --> 00:57:35,320
Send someone to change them now.

594
00:57:35,400 --> 00:57:38,960
Oh, the staff
must've grabbed the wrong box.

595
00:57:39,840 --> 00:57:41,840
Oh, here it is.

596
00:57:42,360 --> 00:57:44,360
Sorry.

597
00:57:44,440 --> 00:57:45,920
What should I do?

598
00:57:46,000 --> 00:57:47,800
They're delivering a bridal dress
right now.

599
00:57:47,880 --> 00:57:49,320
They won't make it in time.

600
00:57:50,760 --> 00:57:52,280
What about this?

601
00:57:52,360 --> 00:57:54,920
You're going to pass by my condo anyway.

602
00:57:55,000 --> 00:57:56,320
Can you come pick it up?

603
00:57:56,840 --> 00:57:59,120
I think this is the best way.

604
00:58:00,720 --> 00:58:02,000
Nothing ever goes my way.

605
00:58:02,080 --> 00:58:03,480
Well…

606
00:58:03,560 --> 00:58:05,960
Mistakes can happen.

607
00:58:06,040 --> 00:58:08,720
Don't be mad. I'll prepare it for you.

608
00:58:51,120 --> 00:58:51,960
Yiwa!

609
00:58:53,240 --> 00:58:54,280
May?

610
00:58:54,360 --> 00:58:56,680
- How long has this been going on?
- Wait.

611
00:58:59,560 --> 00:59:01,280
Help me. It hurts.

612
00:59:01,960 --> 00:59:02,800
After everything I gave you,

613
00:59:02,880 --> 00:59:04,680
- you steal my man?
- Enough.

614
00:59:04,760 --> 00:59:06,360
- Yiwa!
- I said stop.

615
00:59:06,440 --> 00:59:07,960
What's your problem?

616
00:59:08,840 --> 00:59:10,080
Are you going to kill her?

617
00:59:11,160 --> 00:59:12,760
Yiwa!

618
00:59:12,840 --> 00:59:14,200
You!

619
00:59:14,280 --> 00:59:15,800
Maysa, stop!

620
00:59:16,400 --> 00:59:17,600
Are you insane?

621
00:59:17,680 --> 00:59:20,600
You pick her over me? What am I to you?

622
00:59:21,200 --> 00:59:23,160
What am I to you?

623
00:59:23,240 --> 00:59:25,680
You bastard!

624
00:59:28,240 --> 00:59:29,720
You asked for it.

625
00:59:34,080 --> 00:59:35,840
You're only good on screen.

626
00:59:35,920 --> 00:59:38,160
In bed, you're useless.

627
00:59:38,760 --> 00:59:41,000
I'll sleep with whoever I want!

628
00:59:47,880 --> 00:59:48,720
Damn it.

629
01:00:01,000 --> 01:00:04,480
I've been his woman for a long time.

630
01:00:05,600 --> 01:00:07,720
You and me, we're the same.

631
01:00:08,880 --> 01:00:11,640
You can slap me. I can slap you too.

632
01:00:24,520 --> 01:00:25,800
You came for this, didn't you?

633
01:00:29,400 --> 01:00:30,840
Take it and leave.

634
01:01:15,680 --> 01:01:16,880
Aey.

635
01:01:17,800 --> 01:01:19,520
I'm reopening this case.

636
01:01:20,520 --> 01:01:23,800
We have to bring the person
who did this to Kul to justice.

637
01:01:23,880 --> 01:01:25,680
You're kind of heavy, you know.

638
01:01:26,800 --> 01:01:28,400
Hey! Then put me down.

639
01:01:28,480 --> 01:01:29,720
I'm just kidding.

640
01:01:32,800 --> 01:01:36,360
Excuse me. I'm going
to take my wife to bed now.

641
01:01:45,920 --> 01:01:47,720
You're this disgusting

642
01:01:47,800 --> 01:01:49,080
and you dare mess with my sister?

643
01:01:49,880 --> 01:01:51,880
I'm really disappointed
that I trusted you.

644
01:01:52,840 --> 01:01:55,880
<i>I can't stand living in the same world</i>
<i>as you anymore, Wayu.</i>

645
01:01:57,080 --> 01:01:58,000
You Mad Dogs!

646
01:01:58,080 --> 01:01:59,440
Stop!

647
01:02:58,640 --> 01:03:00,680
Subtitle translation by: Panuwat Baikeawon
